<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-23T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-23T03:00:00-05:00" n="1389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1389">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.0015/9–2349: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-23T16:00:00+08:00">September
                                    23, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 23—5:44 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4008. Re Cantel 1142, sent Shanghai 545. APL Shanghai informs Consulate
                            General no holders Chinese passports booked on <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>, but have booked approximately 20 persons Chinese birth
                            who hold foreign passports or IRO stateless travel documents in lieu
                            passports.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department; repeated Canton 1128, Taipei 306, Hong Kong 269.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>